“My father and uncles were all entrepreneurs. All my life I’ve seen the struggles, the long hours, the successes and the failures they experienced, so I knew that starting a business didn’t mean achieving automatic wealth,” she says. Together with a group of five fellow graduates, she launched Gambit Films in 2009, which now makes a turnover “in the millions”. The independent film and media house, which is now known for films such as the globally acclaimed Ellen: The Ellen Pakkies Story, Noem My Skollie and the soapie Suidooster, started out in a bedroom-turned-office. 